Chuck Grassley’s public town halls are at places and times that make it difficult for most Iowans to attend

UPDATE: This document has been updated with with historical data on Senator Grassley’s town halls since 2011 and town halls held or schedule through February 2018. The previous version is available here.

Senator Chuck Grassley famously claims he visits all 99 Iowa counties every year. The “full Grassley” has become a standard other politicians try to meet, and some do. It’s interesting, however, that Grassley isn’t quite as accessible as he would have you think.

It’s been pointed out that Grassley counts a mixture of public and private events, and the public events tend to be in relatively remote locations far from Iowa’s population centers. In fact, according to this source, since 2011

Senator Grassley has not held an open public event as part of his annual 99 county tour in nearly all of the state’s major population centers, including no public meetings in Polk, Linn, or 8 of Iowa’s most populous 10 counties.

Let’s take a look at the 13 town halls Senator Grassley has held or scheduled since August 2017.

The first thing to note is that most of these fall during normal working hours for most of Mr. Grassley’s constituents, which means they would have to miss work in order to meet with their senator. The only exception was a Saturday morning town hall held in Sac County.

The other thing that is striking is where Mr. Grassley has scheduled his public town halls. As the following map shows, Mr. Grassley’s public town hall meetings tend to be in rural areas far from most of Iowa’s population centers. A possible exception was the town hall held in Boone, which is relatively close to the more heavily populated Dallas, Polk, Story, and Webster counties, but still a 50-mile drive (each way) from Des Moines.

Grassley town halls vs population

Click on the town hall markers and counties for more information.

Mr. Grassley is a strong supporter of Donald Trump, so it’s also interesting to look at how well Trump did in these counties in the 2016 election. The answer is very well. Trump won all of the counties hosting Grassley’s public town halls, and got more than 60% of the vote in all but Boone County.

Grassley town halls vs Trump vote %

Click on town hall markers and counties for more information.

So it looks like Mr. Grassley is continuing to play it safe, holding public meetings in only heavily Republican areas, far from where most of his constituents live, and at times that would require even most local constituents to miss work in order to attend.

It appears the 99-county “full Grassley” may not be quite what is used to be.
